@NODE "Maineng" "Insert_Ascii 1.01 for FinalCopy/Finalwriter"
@TOC "MAIN"

                  @{fg shine}ģInsert_Ascii 1.01Ģ@{fg text}

is an ARexx script for Finalwriter or FinalCopyII to include an ASCII file
to your existing document.


                           @{" " link "Vorworteng"} Some words

                           @{" " link "Installeng"} Installation

                           @{" " link "Benutzeng"} Usage

                           @{" " link "Sonsteng"} Author

                           @{" " link "Histeng"} History

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Vorworteng" "Some words"
@TOC "MAIN"


   This is a further development of Rexx script by Mike Fitzgerald
   (mrfitz@groupz.net).

   My version uses a special routine of "rexxtricks.library". That's why
   my script is 6 times faster than the original.
   (e.g.: File:          24.000 Bytes
          Mike's Script: 12,24 Sec.
          My Script:      2,12 Sec.

   This script is a special version with integrated languages. If your 
   system language is'nt german, so the english version will be used.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installeng" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

SYSTEM:

   Copy all libraries to your LIBS: directory.


FINALWRITER:

1. Copy ģinsert_ascii.fwrexxĢ to your FWMacros-Drawer.

2. Start program ģRexxMastĢ.

3. Start ģFinalwriterĢ or ģFinalCopyIIĢ.

4. Open menu "User - Other - Preferences...". 

         * "Action" - New
         * "Name of menu" - Insert Ascii
         * "Command" - "Type" - ARexx-Script
         * "Command" - "Select" (insert_ascii.fwrexx)
         * "HotKey" - F10
         * "Accept"
         * "Save"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Benutzeng" "Usage"
@TOC "MAIN"

      If you want to include an Ascii file to your document, start this
      script. At the cursor the file will be included.


                                  That's all.

@ENDNODE

